# Add Company to Market Map

When the user asks to add a company to the market map, follow these steps:

## Expected Input Format

The user will provide some or all of:
- **Company name** (required)
- **Sector** (required) — must be one of: Consumer, Infrastructure, Data & Analytics, Enterprise: Horizontal, Enterprise: Vertical, Security, Prosumer, Robotics, DevOps & MLOps, Agents
- **Category** (required) — must match an existing category within the chosen sector (see list below)
- **Shortlist URL** (optional) — defaults to `https://shortlistjobs.com/companies/{slug}` where slug is the lowercased, hyphenated company name

## Valid Sectors and Categories

- **Consumer**: Entertainment, Social, Music, Education, Gaming
- **Infrastructure**: Models, Compute, Vector DBs
- **Data & Analytics**: Data Ops, BI & Insights, Analytics
- **Enterprise: Horizontal**: Sales, Marketing, Design, Engineering
- **Enterprise: Vertical**: Healthcare, Legal, Finance
- **Security**: AI Safety, Privacy, Compliance
- **Prosumer**: Search, Video, Image, 3D & AR
- **Robotics**: Humanoid, Industrial, Autonomous
- **DevOps & MLOps**: ML Platform, Deployment, Monitoring
- **Agents**: Coding, Task Automation, Customer

## Steps

1. Open `data/companies.json`
2. Create a new entry with this schema:
   ```json
   {
     "name": "Company Name",
     "sector": "Sector Name",
     "category": "Category Name",
     "shortlistUrl": "https://shortlistjobs.com/companies/company-slug"
   }
   ```
3. Insert the entry in the correct position — group it with other companies in the same sector and category
4. Save the file

## Example Prompt

> Add company: Anthropic, Infrastructure, Models, https://shortlistjobs.com/companies/anthropic

## Bulk Add

Users may provide multiple companies at once. Add each one following the same rules.

> Add companies:
> - Notion AI, Enterprise: Horizontal, Engineering
> - Vercel, Infrastructure, Compute
> - Scale AI, Data & Analytics, Data Ops
